

## 1.1 git config --global user.name
syntax:git config --global user.name "Your Name"
purpose:Sets or displays the global username used for Git commits.
Example:git config --global user.name "subbu"
screenshot:![Git Username](git-config.png)

## 1.2 git config --global user.email
syntax:git config --global user.email "Your email"
purpose:Sets or displays the global email used for Git commits.
Example:git config --global user.email "n220469@rguktn.ac.in"
screenshot:![Git email](git-config.png)

## 1.3 git config --list
syntax:git config --list
purpose:Displays all Git configuration settings
Example:git config --list
screenshot:![Git Config list Output](git-list.png)

## 1.4 git config --global --unset user.name
syntax:git config --global --unset user.name
purpose:Removes a specific Git configuration setting.
Example:git config --global --unset user.name
screenshot:![Git unset output](git-unset.png)

